The collapse feature is only available for curly brackets and comments, it would be great if also consider adding this feature for region blocks (#region <...> #endregion).

The collapse for comments tag isn't working well for the autohelp header, for example:

{color:#8eb021}<#{color}
{color:#59afe1}.SYNOPSIS{color}
    {color:#8eb021}foo{color}
{color:#59afe1}.DESCRIPTION{color}
    {color:#8eb021}var
     Activities:
         1. Do something in region 1
         2. Do something in region 2
         ...
         n. Do something in region n.{color}
{color:#59afe1}.NOTES{color}
    {color:#8eb021}foovar{color}
{color:#8eb021}#>{color}

As shown in the attached file (Capture.png) it collapse till ".SYNOPSIS". I found a workaround that if something is added before ".SYNOPSIS" it will collapse well, as shown in Capture2.png and Capture3.png files, but I don't know if this could be a problem for powershell script.

Regards,
Tony Briceño

After the evalutation license expired, you cannot change the license.

*Workaround:*

# Shutdown Bamboo.
# Edit <Bamboo-Home>/bamboo.cfg.xml file and find the following line, {code}
          <property name="license.string">YOUR_CURRENT_LICENSE_KEY</property>
      {code}
# Replace the line with,
      {code}
          <property name="license.string">YOUR_NEW_LICENSE_KEY</property>
      {code}
# Restart Bamboo.

*PS* You also need to escape < and > characters in XML file. If you have < in your license key use {{&lt;}} and for > use  {{&gt;}}

